text:
How do I get my frame listed in the Warpcast Explore section?

1. Must be a v2 frame

2. Frame needs to open smoothly and quickly

3. Frame *should not* prompt to connect a wallet other than the Frames v2 Wagmi connector. Bad UX for users.

4. Properly sized frame icon

5. Has a valid and complete manifest (see link)

6. Publicly casted by the creator (feel free to DC the cast)

https://docs.farcaster.xyz/developers/frames/v2/notifications_webhooks#create-a-farcaster-domain-manifest

cast.text:
New on Warpcast: revamped frames tab

- Access your favorite frame in 2 taps
- Tap a frame to launch it
- Tap Explore to access the growing list of v2 frames
- You can add any v2 frame in your feed; remove a frame with long press
- Replaces the old Explore tab
- Live on mobile; no immediate plans for web

Frames can now send notifications!

- When you add a frame, it will have the ability to send you in-app notifications on Warpcast

- Turn off notifications or remove a frame by long pressing the frame icon on the frames tab

- Only frames you explicitly "add" to Warpcast can send notifications; simply using a frame does not grant notifications permissions
